cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning, specifically on the use of convolutional neural networks for texture generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of neural networks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to understand the behavior of neural networks, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the generation of images, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
